Backend for Hospital Billing System
Prerequisites:

Node.js must be installed

Instructions for initial setup:

Open your terminal and navigate to the project directory
Run the command npm install to install all the required dependencies
Start the server by running the command node server.js. The server will run on port 5000.
Use the following JSON format to store a new entry:


{
    "patient": {
        "name": "NAME",
        "address": "ADDRESS"
    },
    "hospital": {
        "name": "HOSPITAL"
    },
    "date": "DATE",
    "bill": AMOUNT
}

To access all the entries, send a GET request to localhost:5000/items.

To retrieve specific entries, you can send a GET request to localhost:5000/items/search endpoint with the desired search parameter. 
You can search by name, hospital, date, bill, or address. 
The format for the GET request would be localhost:5000/items/search?parameter=value.